River Dreams
============
A prompt for the ZSH shell (Linux only) with a tribal design. It displays:

    - Your local IPV4 address.
    - The disk use percentage.
    - The battery percentage and its status, if any.
    - The day of the week, month and day of the month.
    - The hour and minute.
    - A decorator when root.
    - A decorator for exit codes.
    - The directory path.

Requirements
------------
In order to build it, you will need:

    - a C compiler.
    - noto fonts.
    - a font patched by the Nerd Fonts project.

Installation
------------
- Compile the file river-dreams.c.

    mkdir -p ~/.local/bin
    cc -O3 -o ~/.local/bin/river-dreams river-dreams.c

- Make its output be your ZSH prompt by editing your ~/.zshrc file.

    setopt promptsubst
    PROMPT='$(~/.local/bin/river-dreams)'

- Reopen ZSH.

